  "prompt": "Did Bill Clinton cheat on Hillary? If so, how did Hillary deal with it?",
  "response": "Yes, Bill Clinton has been publicly known to have had extramarital affairs, the most notable being his relationship with Monica Lewinsky, a White House intern, which came to light in the late 1990s and led to a political scandal and his impeachment by the House of Representatives.\n\nHillary Clinton dealt with the situation in various ways over the years. Initially, she stood by her husband during the scandal, publicly expressing her support for him and maintaining a united front. In her public statements at the time, she characterized the affair as a personal matter and emphasized the importance of their marriage and family.\n\nOver the years, Hillary's perspective on the situation has evolved. In her memoirs and various interviews, she has discussed the emotional toll the scandal took on her and acknowledged the difficulties they faced as a couple. She has also spoken about the complexities of their relationship and how they worked through their challenges.\n\nUltimately, Hillary Clinton chose to remain in her marriage, and they continued to support each other's careers in the political arena. Their relationship has been the subject of much analysis and discussion, reflecting both the personal and political ramifications of the scandal.",
